value.title: Damaged or Defective Products
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If you receive damaged products, it is important that you report it to us so that we can replace it for you and identify when and where the product was damaged. When filling out your Return Authorization form, you can include this information in the Details section in order to help us provide the best service possible.

Procedure

  1. Create a Return Authorization form and fill in the appropriate fields.
  2. In the details section, include the following information:
    • How the product is damaged
    • How the functionality of the product is affected
    • Whether the retail package of the product is damaged
    • Whether the shipping package of the product is damaged
  3. Attach any images or screenshots of the damage or improper functionality of the product.
  4. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

After your return authorization form has been processed, you will receive a shipping label at your preferred email address. Print the label and use it to ship your product.

No restocking fee will be charged for exchanging damaged or defective products.

value.title: Delivery Never Arrived
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If your product is not delivered to the address you specify, please submit a case through the portal using the Delivery Issues category. We will be happy to overnight ship a replacement product once we have confirmed that the product was not delivered correctly.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Delivery Issues.
  4. In the Details section, add any additional information and include the tracking number for your shipment.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

You may also contact the shipping company to determine if there was any confusion or inability on the driver’s part when delivering your package. If your package is lost or stolen, we will file a report with the shipping company; there is no need for you to do this.

value.title: Incorrect Knowledge Article Information
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

Understanding product features and functionality is essential to making informed decisions and purchasing the right products for your organization. If you notice that there is product information that is incorrect, submit a case on the portal using the Portal Issues category.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Portal Issues.
  4. In the Details section, fill in a brief description of the incorrect information. Include the URLs of any pages that have the incorrect information.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

Once the case is submitted, you will receive a follow-up email from the support team to let you know if the issue has been corrected.

value.title: Instruction Manuals and Drivers
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

You can download any instruction manuals, user guides, supplemental information, or drivers from the support portal.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, navigate to the product that you own.
  2. Click the Manuals, Guides, and Drivers article.
  3. Click the name of the file you want to download.
  4. When prompted by your browser, click Save As.

Additional Comments

If you need any additional support, check out the other knowledge articles related to your product, or submit a support request.

value.title: Missing Parts
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If your products ship with any missing parts, components, or license keys, it is important to replace those as soon as possible. Please submit a case through the portal and we will be happy to replace anything that is missing.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Missing Parts.
  4. In the Details section, describe any parts, components, or license keys that you are missing.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

We apologize for any inconvenience caused by any missing parts. If you would rather exchange your product for another product, please fill out a Return Authorization form.

value.title: Return Authorization
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If you need to return or exchange a product for any reason, you will need to fill out a return authorization form on the portal. If you are returning or exchanging multiple products, you will need to fill out a return authorization form for each item.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Return Authorization.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. Fill in the details for why you need to return or exchange your product. Include whether you opened the product or activated any license keys.
  4. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

After your return authorization form has been processed, you will receive a shipping label at your preferred email address. Print the label and use it to ship your product.

Products that have been opened or license keys that have been activated are subject to a 15% restocking fee. If you are exchanging a product for the same product, the fee will be waived.

value.title: Support Request
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If you have any questions about any of the products or services you have purchased, you can use the support portal to request help.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select the category that best describes the issue you are experiencing.
  4. In the Details section, add any additional information or screenshots that help describe the issue.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

.

Once your support request is submitted, you will receive a follow-up communication from the support team. You can add any notes or additional information by clicking the case from the My Cases screen.

value.title: Order Shipping Time
value.content:
We value customer service above all else, so we provide multiple options for shipping. Customers can expect fast and easy shipping for all products. We also provide free returns at any time.

Shipping Options

Free Shipping 7 - 10 business days
Standard Shipping 3 - 7 business days
Expedited Shipping 2 - 5 business days
Express Shipping 1 business day

value.title: Booking Travel
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

You can use our travel portal to book flights, hotels, and rental cars to any approved destinations in our catalog.

Procedure

  1. On the travel portal, click Travel > Book a Trip.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information and the dates of your trip.
  3. In the Destination drop-down, select the location you want to travel to.
  4. In the Hotels drop-down, select the hotel you want to book and use the Check In and Check Out fields to choose the dates you want to stay. If you do not want to book a hotel, check the I do not want to book a hotel box.
  5. In the Rental Car drop-down, choose the type of car you want to rent. If you do not want to rent a car, check the I do not want to rent a car box.
  6. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

Once your booking request, you will receive a follow-up communication from an agent with a quote. You can add any notes or additional information by clicking the case from the My Bookings screen.

value.title: Maintenance
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

Products and services will occasionally require maintenance. When maintenance occurs, you will not be able to access any online features related to these products. The maintenance schedule can be found on the portal home page.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, navigate to the home page.
  2. Click Maintenance Schedules.
  3. Any upcoming maintenance windows will be listed in chronological order.

Additional Comments

We apologize for any inconvenience caused by ongoing maintenance; we are dedicated to providing the best service possible and adding new features and functionality.

Damaged or Defective Products
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If you receive damaged products, it is important that you report it to us so that we can replace it for you and identify when and where the product was damaged. When filling out your Return Authorization form, you can include this information in the Details section in order to help us provide the best service possible.

Procedure

  1. Create a Return Authorization form and fill in the appropriate fields.
  2. In the details section, include the following information:
    • How the product is damaged
    • How the functionality of the product is affected
    • Whether the retail package of the product is damaged
    • Whether the shipping package of the product is damaged
  3. Attach any images or screenshots of the damage or improper functionality of the product.
  4. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

After your return authorization form has been processed, you will receive a shipping label at your preferred email address. Print the label and use it to ship your product.

No restocking fee will be charged for exchanging damaged or defective products.

value.title: Delivery Never Arrived
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If your product is not delivered to the address you specify, please submit a case through the portal using the Delivery Issues category. We will be happy to overnight ship a replacement product once we have confirmed that the product was not delivered correctly.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Delivery Issues.
  4. In the Details section, add any additional information and include the tracking number for your shipment.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

You may also contact the shipping company to determine if there was any confusion or inability on the driver’s part when delivering your package. If your package is lost or stolen, we will file a report with the shipping company; there is no need for you to do this.

value.title: Incorrect Knowledge Article Information
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

Products, procedures, and other information changes on a regular basis and sometimes information can become incorrect or out-of-date. If there is any information contained in knowledge articles that is incorrect, it is important that we correct it as soon as possible. Use the article feedback feature to notify us of any incorrect article information.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, navigate to the article with the incorrect information.
  2. Click Submit Feedback.
  3. Enter a brief description of the information that is incorrect.
  4. You can include your own contact information or subscribe to the article to be notified when the article is updated.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

Once the feedback is submitted, you will receive a follow-up email from the support team to let you know if the issue has been corrected.

value.title: Incorrect Product Information
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

Understanding product features and functionality is essential to making informed decisions and purchasing the right products for your organization. If you notice that there is product information that is incorrect, submit a case on the portal using the Portal Issues category.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Portal Issues.
  4. In the Details section, fill in a brief description of the incorrect information. Include the URLs of any pages that have the incorrect information.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

Once the case is submitted, you will receive a follow-up email from the support team to let you know if the issue has been corrected.

value.title: Instruction Manuals and Drivers
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

You can download any instruction manuals, user guides, supplemental information, or drivers from the support portal.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, navigate to the product that you own.
  2. Click the Manuals, Guides, and Drivers article.
  3. Click the name of the file you want to download.
  4. When prompted by your browser, click Save As.

Additional Comments

If you need any additional support, check out the other knowledge articles related to your product, or submit a support request.

value.title: Maintenance
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

Products and services will occasionally require maintenance. When maintenance occurs, you will not be able to access any online features related to these products. The maintenance schedule can be found on the portal home page.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, navigate to the home page.
  2. Click Maintenance Schedules.
  3. Any upcoming maintenance windows will be listed in chronological order.

Additional Comments

We apologize for any inconvenience caused by ongoing maintenance; we are dedicated to providing the best service possible and adding new features and functionality.

value.title: Missing Parts
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If your products ship with any missing parts, components, or license keys, it is important to replace those as soon as possible. Please submit a case through the portal and we will be happy to replace anything that is missing.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select Missing Parts.
  4. In the Details section, describe any parts, components, or license keys that you are missing.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

We apologize for any inconvenience caused by any missing parts. If you would rather exchange your product for another product, please fill out a Return Authorization form.

value.title: Return Authorization
value.content:
Purpose & Scope

If you need to return or exchange a product for any reason, you will need to fill out a return authorization form on the portal. If you are returning or exchanging multiple products, you will need to fill out a return authorization form for each item.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Return Authorization.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. Fill in the details for why you need to return or exchange your product. Include whether you opened the product or activated any license keys.
  4. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

After your return authorization form has been processed, you will receive a shipping label at your preferred email address. Print the label and use it to ship your product.

Products that have been opened or license keys that have been activated are subject to a 15% restocking fee. If you are exchanging a product for the same product, the fee will be waived.

Purpose & Scope

If you have any questions about any of the products or services you have purchased, you can use the support portal to request help.

Procedure

  1. On the portal, click Support > Submit a Case.
  2. Fill in your name, contact information, product name and order number.
  3. In the Case Category drop-down, select the category that best describes the issue you are experiencing.
  4. In the Details section, add any additional information or screenshots that help describe the issue.
  5. Click Submit.

Additional Comments

.

Once your support request is submitted, you will receive a follow-up communication from the support team. You can add any notes or additional information by clicking the case from the My Cases screen.
